- [ ] 0.2 Generate inventory JSON for Codex, vault, and native stores.
  Command:
  ~~~powershell
  $ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'
  function Get-StoreInventory {
    param([string]$StoreName, [string]$Root, [string[]]$ExcludeNames = @())
    Get-ChildItem -LiteralPath $Root -Directory | Where-Object { $ExcludeNames -notcontains $_.Name } | ForEach-Object {
      $isRp = [bool]($_.Attributes -band [System.IO.FileAttributes]::ReparsePoint)
      $target = $null
      if ($isRp) { $target = (Get-Item -LiteralPath $_.FullName).Target }
      [pscustomobject]@{ Store = $StoreName; Name = $_.Name; Path = $_.FullName; IsReparsePoint = $isRp; Target = $target }
    }
  }
  $all = @()
  $all += Get-StoreInventory -StoreName 'codex' -Root 'C:\Users\DaveWitkin\.codex\skills'
  $all += Get-StoreInventory -StoreName 'vault' -Root 'C:\Users\DaveWitkin\.opencode-lazy-vault' -ExcludeNames @('.system','_archived_skills')
  $all += Get-StoreInventory -StoreName 'native' -Root 'C:\Users\DaveWitkin\.config\opencode\skill'
  $all | Sort-Object Store, Name | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 6 | Set-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\inventory-before.json' -Encoding utf8
  ~~~
  Authoritative acceptance check:
  ~~~powershell
  $inv = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\inventory-before.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  (($inv | Where-Object { $_.Store -eq 'codex' }).Count -ge 72) -and (($inv | Where-Object { $_.Store -eq 'vault' }).Count -ge 70) -and (($inv | Where-Object { $_.Store -eq 'native' }).Count -ge 8)
  ~~~
  Expected output: `True`.
  Diagnostic checks: inspect `inventory-before.json` if counts differ from verified facts.
  Error recovery: If counts differ, continue only after documenting the changed counts in the execution log.

- [ ] 0.3 Compute canonical target map and conflict report.
  Command:
  ~~~powershell
  $ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'
  $inv = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\inventory-before.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  $vault = @{}; $native = @{}
  $inv | Where-Object Store -eq 'vault' | ForEach-Object { $vault[$_.Name] = $_ }
  $inv | Where-Object Store -eq 'native' | ForEach-Object { $native[$_.Name] = $_ }
  $names = @($vault.Keys + $native.Keys | Sort-Object -Unique)
  $map = foreach ($name in $names) {
    $v = $vault[$name]; $n = $native[$name]
    $target = $null; $status = 'ok'; $reason = $null
    if ($v -and $n) {
      $nativePath = $n.Path
      if ($v.IsReparsePoint -and ($v.Target -eq $nativePath -or ($v.Target -is [array] -and $v.Target -contains $nativePath))) { $target = $nativePath; $reason = 'vault-junction-points-to-native' }
      elseif (-not $v.IsReparsePoint -and -not $n.IsReparsePoint) { $status = 'conflict'; $reason = 'vault-and-native-are-separate-real-folders' }
      else { $target = $nativePath; $reason = 'both-exist-default-to-native-per-rule' }
    } elseif ($v) { $target = $v.Path; $reason = 'vault-only' }
    elseif ($n) { $target = $n.Path; $reason = 'native-only' }
    [pscustomobject]@{ Name = $name; CanonicalTarget = $target; Status = $status; Reason = $reason }
  }
  $map | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 6 | Set-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\canonical-target-map.json' -Encoding utf8
  ~~~
  Authoritative acceptance check:
  ~~~powershell
  $map = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\canonical-target-map.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  ($map | Where-Object { $_.Status -eq 'conflict' }).Count
  ~~~
  Expected output: `0` unless new true conflicts exist.
  Diagnostic checks: manually inspect conflict rows if output is not `0`.
  Error recovery: If conflicts exist, stop before any destructive action and ask the user to choose canonical targets.

Exit criteria: `precondition-paths.json`, `inventory-before.json`, and `canonical-target-map.json` exist, and true conflicts are zero or explicitly resolved by the user.

