## Phase 1: Backup Real Codex Folders That Will Be Converted

Objective: Create a timestamped, auditable backup of every real Codex folder whose name has a canonical vault/native target.

- [ ] 1.1 Create backup directory and backup manifest.
  Command:
  ~~~powershell
  $ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'
  $stamp = Get-Date -Format 'yyyy-MM-dd-HHmmss'
  $backupRoot = "C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\backups\$stamp-pre-edit"
  New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path $backupRoot | Out-Null
  $inv = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\inventory-before.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  $map = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\canonical-target-map.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  $names = @($map | Where-Object { $_.Status -eq 'ok' } | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Name)
  $toBackup = $inv | Where-Object { $_.Store -eq 'codex' -and -not $_.IsReparsePoint -and ($names -contains $_.Name) }
  $manifest = foreach ($item in $toBackup) {
    $dest = Join-Path $backupRoot $item.Name
    Copy-Item -LiteralPath $item.Path -Destination $dest -Recurse -Force
    [pscustomobject]@{ Name = $item.Name; Source = $item.Path; Backup = $dest; BackedUpAt = (Get-Date).ToString('o') }
  }
  $manifest | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 5 | Set-Content -LiteralPath (Join-Path $backupRoot 'backup-manifest.json') -Encoding utf8
  $backupRoot | Set-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\backup-dir.txt' -Encoding utf8
  ~~~
  Authoritative acceptance check:
  ~~~powershell
