- [ ] 2.3 Replace each safe real Codex duplicate folder with a junction.
  Command:
  ~~~powershell
  $ErrorActionPreference = 'Stop'
  $conversion = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\conversion-list.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  $safe = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\duplicate-safety-results.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json | Where-Object { $_.Status -eq 'convertible' }
  $safeNames = @($safe | Select-Object -ExpandProperty Name)
  $log = foreach ($c in ($conversion | Where-Object { $safeNames -contains $_.Name })) {
    $item = Get-Item -LiteralPath $c.CodexPath
    if ($item.Attributes -band [System.IO.FileAttributes]::ReparsePoint) { [pscustomobject]@{ Name=$c.Name; Action='skip-already-junction'; Path=$c.CodexPath; Target=$c.CanonicalTarget; IsReparsePoint=$true }; continue }
    Remove-Item -LiteralPath $c.CodexPath -Recurse -Force
    cmd /c mklink /j "$($c.CodexPath)" "$($c.CanonicalTarget)" | Out-Null
    $newItem = Get-Item -LiteralPath $c.CodexPath
    [pscustomobject]@{ Name=$c.Name; Action='converted'; Path=$c.CodexPath; Target=(Get-Item -LiteralPath $c.CodexPath).Target; IsReparsePoint=[bool]($newItem.Attributes -band [System.IO.FileAttributes]::ReparsePoint) }
  }
  $log | ConvertTo-Json -Depth 6 | Set-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\conversion-log.json' -Encoding utf8
  ~~~
  Authoritative acceptance check:
  ~~~powershell
  $log = Get-Content -LiteralPath 'C:\development\opencode\.conductor\tracks\20260702-codex-skill-symlinks\conversion-log.json' -Raw | ConvertFrom-Json
  ($log | Where-Object { -not $_.IsReparsePoint }).Count
  ~~~
  Expected output: `0`.
  Diagnostic checks: spot check one converted folder with `Get-Item -LiteralPath 'C:\Users\DaveWitkin\.codex\skills\agent-writer' | Select-Object FullName, Target, Attributes` if `agent-writer` was converted.
  Error recovery: If junction creation fails after removal, restore the folder with `Copy-Item -LiteralPath <BackupPath> -Destination <CodexPath> -Recurse -Force`, then stop.

Exit criteria: Every safe conversion entry is now a reparse point and has a recorded target.

